    • FAQs

      Questions you may have, answered with
      • How does print quality differ among Xerox models?
        Print quality in Xerox printers can differ based on resolution and technology used. Models designed for professional use typically offer higher resolution and color accuracy than basic models. Consider laser printers for sharper text and inkjet models for high-quality color prints.
        How'd we do?
        Leave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tabLeave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tab
      • What are the benefits of multifunction Xerox printers?
        Multifunction Xerox printers combine printing, scanning, copying, and sometimes faxing into one device, offering a compact solution for workspace optimization. They are ideal for offices with limited space and for users who need versatile functionality from their devices.
        How'd we do?
        Leave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tabLeave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tab
      • How do Xerox printers support mobile and remote printing?
        Many Xerox printers support mobile printing through apps like Apple AirPrint, Google Cloud Print, and Xerox Print Service for Android. This feature is crucial for users needing to print from smartphones, tablets, or laptops wirelessly, enhancing convenience and productivity.
